GET     git clone https://github.com/hallwaykid/pw.git ||
        git clone http://repo.or.cz/w/www.git
INSTALL cd pw/ruby     # enter dir
        bundle install # install dependencies
	./install      # make symlink to ruby-lib (rsync/cp it or have gem-tooling do something if you prefer)
USE     cd ..          # {css,js} should be visible so change dirs
        foreman start  # run HTTP and HTTPS daemons on 80/443
NOTES
httpd.ru can be used for other Rack-API servers ('thin' is default, 'unicorn' works well, etc)
to listen on 80/443 (in lieu of >1024 behind apache/nginx/lighttpd)
 $ setcap cap_net_bind_service=+ep `which ruby`

HOST  mkdir domain/hostname
CLEAN rm -rf cache index
